# Conditional clarity

Keep React components declarative. Extract any conditional logic with more than two branches into a named helper, hook, or lookup map.

## Allowed inline

- Single-condition ternaries (`isSolved ? ... : ...`)
- Small inline conditionals for rendering (`isOpen && <Panel />`)

## Extract these

- Nested ternaries or multi-branch business logic inside components
- Any conditional that is difficult to explain in one sentence — put it behind a well-named function

Prefer `if`/`switch`/lookup maps over nested ternaries. Colocate helpers next to consumers; share a module when the same logic is duplicated.
